data.enText: a person who loves their country and who is ready to defend it against an enemy

simple_means.memory_skill: patri 父亲，引申为“祖国” + ot 表人 → 爱国者

tr: one who loves and defends his or her country

value.def: Someone who is a patriot loves their country and feels very loyal towards it.

example.ex: They were staunch British patriots and had portraits of the Queen in their flat.
example.tran: 他们是英国坚定的爱国者，并在公寓里挂着女王的肖像。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = father 父亲 , 引申为“祖国”
rootsaffixes.title: patr(i), pater
